<h2>Protect Handler Demo</h2>

The <a name="protect_demo">protect handler demo</a> shows how to protect marked up nodes from
being expanded.
<p>
<h3> Protect a Marked Up Node</h3>
<b> Description:</b> This example shows the result of protecting emphasized text.  HTML characters
have been encoded so that they will not be expanded.
<p>
<b> Input: </b>&lt;protect markup&gt;Silicon Valley is &lt;em&gt;the&lt;/em&gt; place to program.&lt;/protext&gt;
<p>
<b> Result: </b> <protect markup>Silicon Valley is <em>the</em> place to program.</protect>
<p>
<hr>

<h3> Expand a Marked Up Node</h3>
<b> Description:</b> If the result attribute is used, marked up nodes are expanded in the normal
way.
<p>
<b> Input: </b>&lt;protect result&gt;Silicon Valley is &lt;em&gt;the&lt;/em&gt; place to program.&lt;/protext&gt;
<p>
<b> Result: </b> <protect result>Silicon Valley is <em>the</em> place to program.</protect>
<p>
<footer>

